This paper discusses the use of Multi-Agent Reinforcement Learning (MARL) for emergent communication in agent populations, which falls under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the historical context of language evolution research, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses computational models, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE) or neural networks (cs.NE).
